GORGEOUS Angela Sithole is a blooming actress and can&rsquo;t imagine herself doing anything else.The 23-year-old is on her way to becoming a regular on Mzansi TV screens.She plays the feisty Angel on e.tv&rsquo;s Hustle.The drama series takes viewers through the ins and outs of the turbulent music industry and what people will do to get to the top.Angel is a former child star who is trying to establish herself as a musician without her mum looking over her shoulder.She rebels, leaves home and takes the name Tai Chi.&ldquo;The limelight is all she knows. She&rsquo;s an opportunist who will do anything to reach the top. A hustler in every sense of the word.&ldquo;That&rsquo;s what makes the role challenging,&rdquo; she said.The Soweto-born actress with Zulu and Italian roots told SunBuzz she&rsquo;s privileged to learn from experienced cast members.&ldquo;I&rsquo;d love to do theatre to enhance my craft. My cast members teach me a lot,&rdquo; she said.Her co-stars include Brenda Ngxoli, Masello Motana, Zolisa Xaluva and Mothusi Magano.Angela has also acted in local dramas like Isibaya, Zabalaza and Rockville. Hustle airs on e.tv every Monday at 9.30pm.